• 1 teaspoon baking soda 
• ½ teaspoon salt 
• 1 cup (2 sticks) butter, softened 
• ¾ cup granulated sugar 
• ¾ cup packed brown sugar 
• 1 teaspoon vanilla extract 
• 2 large eggs

The Waning Gibbous is when the Moon is more than half illuminated but with the opposite side to the First Quarter. It is primarily used for growth, repair, and maintenance of multi-cellular organisms by providing cells for growth, wound healing, and replacing old or damaged cells. Meiosis, on the other hand, is a type of sexual reproduction that involves two rounds of cell division to produce four haploid daughter cells. It is used in the production of gametes, or sex cells, by providing genetic diversity. The primary difference between mitosis and meiosis is that mitosis produces two daughter cells with the same genetic content, whereas meiosis produces four daughter cells with half the genetic content of the parent cell.

inputs: Describe a psychological condition called "depersonalization disorder".
targets: Depersonalization disorder is a form of dissociative disorder in which an individual experiences a feeling of being detached from reality or themselves.
